review_blob: Look, it's a light beer. But it's not bad compared to other light beers.  Michelob Ultra was disgusting.  This is a drinkable beer for those who need to count calories or carbs.  No aftertaste or unpleasant taste.  Not a lot of flavor, but hey, it's a light beer.
Supposedly, this Czech beer is the world's oldest pilsner. I didn't like it at all.  Skunky taste.  Highly overrated, if you ask me.
A very tasty, light, clean, crisp brew. Can't find it outside of Cincy.  When I visit I buy some to bring home.  Very drinkable, small 7 oz bottles. A good brew.

Decent drinkable beer.  Small head, dissipates quickly. Clear, amber.  Light taste, slight skunky aftertaste.  I remember it tasting MUCH better on tap in the Dominican Republic (I was there twice).  Perhaps it was fresher there.
Dark amber, almost brown, not clear, translucent, kind of muddy. Good full flavor, no aftertaste, slight sweetness, not bad.
One of the best beers I have ever tasted, if not the best.  I first tasted it 25 years ago, and I never tire of this brew.
Slightly astringent taste, it was OK.  Would drink it, but only if nothing better was available.
Dry beer, I like dit a lot. No aftertaste, just good dry flavor, not too sweet.  I could drink this regularly.  Thumbs up.
